Ho Nguyen An Khang is an Intern Back-end Developer with 0 years of commercial experience, possessing a strong academic foundation in Software Engineering (Bachelor, GPA 8.48) and Computer Science from Ton Duc Thang University and Regensburg University of Applied Sciences. Their core expertise lies in applying OOP principles, Design Patterns, Data Structures, and Algorithms to develop robust REST APIs, focusing on secure authentication, online payments, and cloud-based image storage. Through personal projects, Khang has demonstrated proficiency in full-stack development, including a Spring Boot, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, JWT, Stripe, and AWS S3-powered food ordering website, a Django and ReactJS platform for IMDb actor insights utilizing Selenium and BeautifulSoup for web scraping, and a NodeJS, AWS Lambda, AWS S3, AWS API Gateway, Docker-based cloud document converter. They also led the development of an Android Native English learning app with Firebase Database.
Technically, Khang is proficient in Java, JavaScript, Python, C++, and HTML/CSS. They have hands-on experience with frameworks and libraries such as ReactJS, Bootstrap, Spring Boot, NodeJS, Django, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, JWT, Bulma, Selenium, BeautifulSoup, and Android Native. Their database skills encompass MySQL, MongoDB, SQLite, and Firebase Database. For DevOps and Cloud, Khang is familiar with AWS S3, AWS Lambda, AWS ECS, AWS API Gateway, Docker, and Gitlab, utilizing tools like Stripe, Git, and GitHub. Key domain knowledge includes secure authentication, online payment integration, cloud storage solutions, web scraping techniques, and full-stack web and mobile application development. Khang also possesses advanced English proficiency (IELTS 7.0+).